               <msContents>
                  <summary>F<locus target="#1r"/>-110v: Homiliary in Honor of the Monthly Feast of the Archangel Michael, 20th c Gov Scriptorium. <locus target="#17v"/> mentions the owner, ወልደ ኢያሱስ, and the soul of his father, ወልደ ጊዮርጊስ. <locus target="#23v"/> mentions another owner (?), ወልደ ሰንበት. F<locus target="#24v"/> and passim mention the scribe, ወልደ ኢየሱስ. <locus target="#97v"/> gives his given name, ወልደ ኢየሱስ ኢያቄም, and also his late father, ወልደ ጊዮርጊስ. The illuminations appear to be authentic. </summary>
